  "description": "National flags as emoji. Each card is tested both ways (flag→country and country→flag), tracked separately.",
  "primerTitle": "Flags by region",
  "primer": "Each card pairs a **national flag** with its **country**, tested both ways. The deck covers five regions; here are high-yield anchors and the distinguishing features that prevent mix-ups.\n\n**Europe** — tricolours dominate: France (blue-white-red vertical), Germany (black-red-gold horizontal), Italy (green-white-red vertical), Spain (red-yellow-red with crest). UK → Union Jack; Greece → blue-and-white stripes with corner cross; the Nordics (Sweden, Norway) carry off-centre **Scandinavian crosses**. Catches: **Switzerland** → square red flag with white cross (one of only two square national flags); **Ireland** → green-white-orange, the mirror of Côte d'Ivoire.\n\n**Asia** — Japan → white with a red disc; China → red with five yellow stars; South Korea → white with the red-blue *taegeuk*; India → saffron-white-green with a navy wheel. Catch: **Indonesia** → red over white, the *inverse* of Poland's white over red.\n\n**Africa** — many use the **pan-African colours** (red, green, gold/black): Kenya, Ethiopia, Ghana, South Africa. Egypt → red-white-black with the eagle of Saladin; Morocco → red with a green pentagram; Nigeria → green-white-green.\n\n**Americas** — USA → stars and stripes; Canada → red with the maple leaf; Brazil → green with a yellow rhombus and blue globe; Argentina → light-blue-and-white with the Sun of May. Several Andean flags share red/yellow tones (Colombia, Peru).\n\n**Oceania** — Australia and New Zealand both fly the **Union Jack canton + Southern Cross**; distinguish them by the stars (Australia adds the large Commonwealth Star and uses white stars; NZ's Southern Cross is red with white edges).\n\n**Rule of thumb:** lock onto the distinctive emblem (disc, leaf, cross, star pattern) and the colour order; the classic traps are *inverted* pairs (Poland/Indonesia) and *mirrored* pairs (Ireland/Côte d'Ivoire).",
  "categories": {
